cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with video discriminators in GANs and proposes a new family of discriminators that improve the performance of video GAN models. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the optimization difficulties in unconstrained video discriminator architectures and proposes a more efficient family of discriminators. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with video datasets and proposes a new approach for video generation. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as GANs are a popular AI technique for generating realistic data. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the architecture of video discriminators and proposes a new family of discriminators that improve the performance of GAN models.
